    • Method Detail

      • calcRoute

        public List<? extends PlanElement> calcRoute(Facility fromFacility,
                                             Facility toFacility,
                                             double departureTime,
                                             Person person)
        Description copied from interface: RoutingModule
        Computes a route, as a sequence of plan elements. The plan elements can be only legs, or a sequence of legs and "dummy" activities. All activity types inserted as dummy activities must be notified by the RoutingModule.getStageActivityTypes() method.
        important: if route computation relies on a shortest path algorithm using TravelTime and/or TravelDisutility estimators, this method is responsible for setting the person to the argument person in those estimators before running the shortest path algorithm.
        Specified by:
        calcRoute in interface RoutingModule
        Parameters:
        fromFacility - a Facility representing the departure location
        toFacility - a Facility representing the arrival location
        departureTime - the departure time
        person - the Person to route
        Returns:
        a list of PlanElement, in proper order, representing the trip.

      • getStageActivityTypes

        public StageActivityTypes getStageActivityTypes()
        Description copied from interface: RoutingModule
        Gives access to the activity types to consider as stages.
Specified by:
getStageActivityTypes in interface RoutingModule
Returns:
a non-null StageActivityTypes. This should always return the same instance, or at least return instances which are equal for equals(). Otherwise, replacement of modules in the TripRouter will not work.
